{
  "texts": [
    "However, since the knowledge of pre-trained generative models is fixed after training, methods like retrieval and tool augmentation are needed to acquire new external knowledge.",
    "Research on real-time knowledge acquisition remains limited, making it a valuable area for investigation.Moreover, continually relying on outdated knowledge from language models is inadequate, as models cannot comprehend the significance of given contexts or backgrounds in the current era, thus reducing the reliability of the generated content.",
    "Therefore, updating the information in language models while avoiding the forgetting of existing knowledge, such as through continual learning [301,320], knowledge editing [191,212,303,334], etc., is a topic worth further exploring.",
    "6.2.3 Bias and Fairness.",
    "Since LLMs are often trained on large, unfiltered datasets, GenIR systems may propagate stereotypes and biases present in the data regarding race, culture, and other aspects [68]."
  ]
}